By the way, could you please explain why earth.google.com is prefetching a canvas kit in index.html? What advantages does it provide compared to "embedded" Flutter Web loading?

I'm talking about this comment in their index.html

// This detects Chromium browsers which use a different, smaller version of Canvaskit. This
// preload logic is the same as the actual loading logic built into Flutter.

@slavap 

> By the way, could you please explain why earth.google.com is prefetching a canvas kit in index.html? What advantages does it provide compared to "embedded" Flutter Web loading?

Probably because they haven't switched to the new `flutter_bootstrap.js` yet. They still embed Flutter using `<script src="main.dart.js">`. So they had to write some of the prefetching code by hand. Since `main.dart.js` is quite big, waiting for it to be fetched, parsed, and run would be wasteful.

